FBIS4-34335 "drlat118_a_94026" FBIS-LAT-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Politburo Member Urges Lawyers To Back System Politburo Member Urges Lawyers To Back System FL1706163294 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 17 Jun 94 FL1706163294 Havana Radio Progreso Network Spanish BFN [From the "First Thing" program] [Text] Julian Rizo Alvarez, Politburo member and first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Camaguey, has called on provincial lawyers to support the Unified Vigilance and Protection System. Rizo made the call at a meeting with lawyers, during which it was stressed that the goal of that united effort is to live under the rule of law and to uphold the workers' peace of mind. Rizo said: I ask Camaguey lawyers to honor the virtuous legacy of the nation's founding fathers and the glory gained from loving and defending the fatherland with passion and valor. The meeting included a briefing on the outstanding and decisive performance of these legal workers in detecting and processing cases of illegal purchases and sales of homes and vehicles in accordance with Decree-Law 149.
